dc_title_s: Conservation Easements, Woodland Areas, Annual Reporting: Prince George's County, Maryland
dc_description_s: Woodland Conservation Areas (WCA) are captured to support the annual reporting of the State Forest Conservation Act 0f 1991 by further delineating certain conservation easements into distinct planted, retained, and retained - not credited areas. The source information for each WCA shape is found on approved Type Two Tree Conservation Plans (TCP II), approved by the Prince George’s County Planning Department, for each fiscal year, beginning in 2009.
